  "governance_notes": "All children are leaf nodes with no further decomposition. ParseInput is a pure function with no data store access. PlaceOrder and CancelOrder are atomic operations requiring read_write access to multiple data stores. TrackOrder is a read-only query. Global vars for each child are subsets of parent's available data stores. Data operations cover all parent data needs: orders (read/write), inventory (read/write), payments (read/write)."
